<TITLE> 'Arms trader' arrested at Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Aug 7 (bdnews24.com)RAB on Friday arrested an alleged arms trader after searching a highway coach of Eagle Paribahan at Niribili near Savar. Mohammed Ehtesham, 30, a resident of Mirersorai at Chittagong, admitted that he was carrying a US-made gun with three bullets from Jessore to one 'Akash' in Sobujbagh in the capital. Squadron leader Shah Mizan-ul-Huq of Savar camp of RAB-4 told bdnews24.com the bus was stopped and searched at Niribili on a tip-off. RAB took him to Sobujbagh to hunt down, but could not find him. Sobujbagh police said Akash was convicted in several cases along with one for murder. A case was filed under the Arms Act with the Ashulia Police Station. bdne
